   178	
   179	## 3. Signal Lifecycle
   180	
   181	```
   182	emitted ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñ∫ active ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñ∫ superseded   (replaces: newer signal targets this ID)
   183	                   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñ∫ expired      (expiresAtStep reached via advanceStep)
   184	                   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚ñ∫ resolved     (explicitly resolved via resolve())
   185	```
   186	
   187	| State | Meaning | Terminal? |
   188	|---|---|---|
   189	| `emitted` | Created; not yet acknowledged by any recipient | No |
   190	| `active` | At least one `onSignal` callback has fired for this signal | No |
   191	| `superseded` | A newer signal with `replaces` targeting this ID was emitted | Yes |
   192	| `expired` | `expiresAtStep` passed; the step advanced past the threshold | Yes |
   193	| `resolved` | The signaled condition is no longer relevant; explicitly closed | Yes |
   194	
   195	**Rules:**
   196	- The signal log retains all signals regardless of terminal state; state is updated in-place
   197	- Transitions are one-way; a terminal state cannot transition to another state
   198	- `onSignal` callbacks fire on every transition: `'emitted'`, `'superseded'`, `'expired'`, `'resolved'`
   199	- When `advanceStep()` expires signals, `onSignal` fires with `event='expired'` for each
   200	
