   329	| 1 | Type exports (all interfaces, types, enums) | None |
   330	| 2 | Signal log (in-memory Map, emit, get, query) | Step 1 |
   331	| 3 | State transitions (resolve, supersede) | Step 2 |
   332	| 4 | Suppression (duplicate detection within window) | Step 3 |
   333	| 5 | advanceStep and expiry | Step 3 |
   334	| 6 | onSignal / offSignal callbacks | Step 3 |
   335	| 7 | Audience resolution (selected resolver) | Step 6 |
   336	| 8 | Routing escalation hook | Step 6 |
   337	
   338	**Definition of done:** A specialist handler can emit a confidence signal, a coordinator can receive it via `onSignal`, and an escalation signal can trigger a routing mode request ‚Äî all within a single in-process thread. The four workflow shapes (WF-C1 through WF-C4) are proved in integration tests.
